</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="D9C76503FFE7FFCDFF04EEC4FDF0FD8B" lastPageId="20" lastPageNumber="1499" pageId="18" pageNumber="1497" type="description">
<paragraph id="91623688FFE7FFCBFF04EEC4FC83FAA3" blockId="18.[178,1085,1233,1285]" pageId="18" pageNumber="1497">
Description: Body length 
<quantity id="56259B6DFFE7FFCBFD94EEC4FD9EFB41" box="[546,630,1233,1255]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.7" pageId="18" pageNumber="1497" unit="mm" value="5.7">5.7 mm</quantity>
; length of forebody 
<quantity id="56259B6DFFE7FFCBFCE7EEC4FC4DFB41" box="[849,933,1233,1255]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.2" pageId="18" pageNumber="1497" unit="mm" value="3.2">3.2 mm</quantity>
. Habitus as in 
<figureCitation id="09E62A0DFFE7FFCBFF04EEFAFF14FAA3" box="[178,252,1263,1285]" captionStart="Figs 17-22" captionStartId="19.[178,218,1468,1488]" captionTargetBox="[178,1084,212,1435]" captionTargetId="figure-81@19.[178,1085,212,1445]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="Figs 17-22: Micrillus siamensis nov.sp.: (17) habitus; (18) forebody; (19) male sternite VIII; (20) aedeagus in lateral view; (21) aedeagus in ventral view; (22) aedeagus in dorsal view. Scale bars: 17-18: 1.0 mm; 19-22: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5301297" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5301297/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="1497">Fig. 17</figureCitation>
. Coloration: body reddish; legs and antennae reddish-yellow.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="91623688FFE7FFCBFF04EF01FDFAFA39" blockId="18.[178,1085,1300,1439]" pageId="18" pageNumber="1497">
Head (
<figureCitation id="09E62A0DFFE7FFCBFF4EEF01FEABFA8C" box="[248,323,1300,1322]" captionStart="Figs 17-22" captionStartId="19.[178,218,1468,1488]" captionTargetBox="[178,1084,212,1435]" captionTargetId="figure-81@19.[178,1085,212,1445]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="Figs 17-22: Micrillus siamensis nov.sp.: (17) habitus; (18) forebody; (19) male sternite VIII; (20) aedeagus in lateral view; (21) aedeagus in ventral view; (22) aedeagus in dorsal view. Scale bars: 17-18: 1.0 mm; 19-22: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5301297" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5301297/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="1497">Fig. 18</figureCitation>
) 1.08 times as long as broad, widest across eyes, narrowed behind eyes; posterior angles rather weakly marked; punctation fine and sparse, somewhat more distinct in lateral and posterior portions; microsculpture very shallow. Eyes somewhat shorter than postocular region in dorsal view. Antennomeres IV-VIII distinctly oblong; VIII nearly twice as long as broad.
</paragraph>
<caption id="C5A26600FFE6FFCAFF04EFA9FE3AFA5B" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5301297" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5301297" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5301297/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="1498" startId="19.[178,218,1468,1488]" targetBox="[178,1084,212,1435]" targetPageId="19">
<paragraph id="91623688FFE6FFCAFF04EFA9FE3AFA5B" blockId="19.[178,1086,1468,1533]" pageId="19" pageNumber="1498">
<emphasis id="A3A9EA9AFFE6FFCAFF04EFA9FEFFFA76" bold="true" box="[178,279,1468,1488]" pageId="19" pageNumber="1498">Figs 17-22</emphasis>
: 
<taxonomicName id="56DD4D0BFFE6FFCAFE92EFA9FE3FFA76" authority="Assing, 2013" authorityName="Assing" authorityYear="2013" box="[292,471,1468,1488]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Micrillus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="1498" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="siamensis" status="nov.sp.">
<emphasis id="A3A9EA9AFFE6FFCAFE92EFA9FE3FFA76" box="[292,471,1468,1488]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="1498">Micrillus siamensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="B89A57E1FFE6FFCAFE68EFA9FDCCFA76" box="[478,548,1468,1488]" pageId="19" pageNumber="1498" rank="species">nov.sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
: (
<emphasis id="A3A9EA9AFFE6FFCAFD80EFA9FDA5FA76" bold="true" box="[566,589,1468,1488]" pageId="19" pageNumber="1498">17</emphasis>
) habitus; (
<emphasis id="A3A9EA9AFFE6FFCAFD04EFA9FD39FA76" bold="true" box="[690,721,1468,1488]" pageId="19" pageNumber="1498">18)</emphasis>
forebody; (
<emphasis id="A3A9EA9AFFE6FFCAFC89EFA9FCBEFA76" bold="true" box="[831,854,1468,1488]" pageId="19" pageNumber="1498">19</emphasis>
) male sternite VIII; (
<emphasis id="A3A9EA9AFFE6FFCAFBA9EFA9FBDEFA76" bold="true" box="[1055,1078,1468,1488]" pageId="19" pageNumber="1498">20</emphasis>
) aedeagus in lateral view; (
<emphasis id="A3A9EA9AFFE6FFCAFE11EFC7FE56FA40" bold="true" box="[423,446,1490,1510]" pageId="19" pageNumber="1498">21</emphasis>
) aedeagus in ventral view; (
<emphasis id="A3A9EA9AFFE6FFCAFD71EFC7FD36FA40" bold="true" box="[711,734,1490,1510]" pageId="19" pageNumber="1498">22</emphasis>
) aedeagus in dorsal view. Scale bars: 17-18: 1.0 mm; 19-22: 0.2 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="91623688FFE6FFCDFF04EC19FBD8FF56" blockId="19.[178,1085,1547,1599]" lastBlockId="20.[178,1072,218,240]" lastPageId="20" lastPageNumber="1499" pageId="19" pageNumber="1498">
Pronotum (
<figureCitation id="09E62A0DFFE6FFCAFE93EC1EFE98F987" box="[293,368,1547,1569]" captionStart="Figs 17-22" captionStartId="19.[178,218,1468,1488]" captionTargetBox="[178,1084,212,1435]" captionTargetId="figure-81@19.[178,1085,212,1445]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="Figs 17-22: Micrillus siamensis nov.sp.: (17) habitus; (18) forebody; (19) male sternite VIII; (20) aedeagus in lateral view; (21) aedeagus in ventral view; (22) aedeagus in dorsal view. Scale bars: 17-18: 1.0 mm; 19-22: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5301297" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5301297/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="1498">Fig. 18</figureCitation>
) 1.14 times as long as broad and 1.02 times as broad as head; lateral margins subparallel in anterior two fifths and converging in posterior three fifths in dorsal view; posterior margin distinctly concave; punctation extremely fine and very dense.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="91623688FFE1FFCDFF04EB15FC64FEF6" blockId="20.[178,1086,256,336]" pageId="20" pageNumber="1499">
Elytra (
<figureCitation id="09E62A0DFFE1FFCDFEB5EB15FEB9FEB0" box="[259,337,256,278]" captionStart="Figs 17-22" captionStartId="19.[178,218,1468,1488]" captionTargetBox="[178,1084,212,1435]" captionTargetId="figure-81@19.[178,1085,212,1445]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="Figs 17-22: Micrillus siamensis nov.sp.: (17) habitus; (18) forebody; (19) male sternite VIII; (20) aedeagus in lateral view; (21) aedeagus in ventral view; (22) aedeagus in dorsal view. Scale bars: 17-18: 1.0 mm; 19-22: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5301297" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5301297/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="1499">Fig. 18</figureCitation>
) approximately as long as pronotum; punctation extremely dense and fine; surface almost matt. Hind wings completely developed. Protarsomeres I-IV not dilated. Metatarsomere I nearly as long as the combined length of II-IV.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="91623688FFE1FFCDFF04EB75FD8EFE35" blockId="20.[178,1085,352,403]" pageId="20" pageNumber="1499">Abdomen with rather dense and fine punctation; interstices with iridescent microsculpture; posterior margin with palisade fringe.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="91623688FFE1FFCDFF71EBB6FDF0FD8B" blockId="20.[178,1085,418,557]" pageId="20" pageNumber="1499">
: sternite VIII (
<figureCitation id="09E62A0DFFE1FFCDFED4EBB7FE45FE1E" box="[354,429,418,440]" captionStart="Figs 17-22" captionStartId="19.[178,218,1468,1488]" captionTargetBox="[178,1084,212,1435]" captionTargetId="figure-81@19.[178,1085,212,1445]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="Figs 17-22: Micrillus siamensis nov.sp.: (17) habitus; (18) forebody; (19) male sternite VIII; (20) aedeagus in lateral view; (21) aedeagus in ventral view; (22) aedeagus in dorsal view. Scale bars: 17-18: 1.0 mm; 19-22: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5301297" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5301297/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="1499">Fig. 19</figureCitation>
) of similar shape as in 
<taxonomicName id="56DD4D0BFFE1FFCDFD16EBB6FCE4FE1E" baseAuthorityName="Eppelsheim" baseAuthorityYear="1890" box="[672,780,418,440]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Micrillus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="1499" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="indicus">
<emphasis id="A3A9EA9AFFE1FFCDFD16EBB6FCE4FE1E" box="[672,780,418,440]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="1499">M. indicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, with narrow and rather deep posterior incision; aedeagus (
<figureCitation id="09E62A0DFFE1FFCDFE68EBAAFDA7FE73" box="[478,591,447,469]" captionStart="Figs 17-22" captionStartId="19.[178,218,1468,1488]" captionTargetBox="[178,1084,212,1435]" captionTargetId="figure-81@19.[178,1085,212,1445]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="Figs 17-22: Micrillus siamensis nov.sp.: (17) habitus; (18) forebody; (19) male sternite VIII; (20) aedeagus in lateral view; (21) aedeagus in ventral view; (22) aedeagus in dorsal view. Scale bars: 17-18: 1.0 mm; 19-22: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5301297" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5301297/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="1499">Figs 20-22</figureCitation>
) minute in relation to body size, 
<quantity id="56259B6DFFE1FFCDFC11EBAAFBEAFE73" box="[935,1026,447,469]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.9" pageId="20" pageNumber="1499" unit="mm" value="0.39">0.39 mm</quantity>
long, distinctly asymmetric; apex of ventral process in ventral view with short process on either side and concave in the middle; sclerotized internal structure curved and apically with three finger-shaped processes.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="D9C76503FFE1FFCDFF04E829FC28FD6E" pageId="20" pageNumber="1499" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="91623688FFE1FFCDFF04E829FC28FD6E" blockId="20.[178,1085,572,712]" pageId="20" pageNumber="1499">
Comparative notes: In general appearance, 
<taxonomicName id="56DD4D0BFFE1FFCDFD48E828FC6BFDF4" authorityName="Assing" authorityYear="2013" box="[766,899,573,594]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Micrillus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="1499" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="siamensis">
<emphasis id="A3A9EA9AFFE1FFCDFD48E828FC6BFDF4" box="[766,899,573,594]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="1499">M. siamensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
somewhat resembles 
<taxonomicName id="56DD4D0BFFE1FFCDFF52E84EFEBAFDD6" baseAuthorityName="Eppelsheim" baseAuthorityYear="1890" box="[228,338,602,624]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Micrillus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="1499" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="indicus">
<emphasis id="A3A9EA9AFFE1FFCDFF52E84EFEBAFDD6" box="[228,338,602,624]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="1499">M. indicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, to which it is closely related, as can be inferred particularly from the similar male sexual characters (shape of male sternite VIII; minute aedeagus of similar general morphology). It differs, however, by distinctly larger body size, the more oblong head, the finer punctation of the pronotum, and by the shape of the aedeagus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
